items.name: Efficient-Page-replacent-stimulator
items.description: 💡 What is Page Replacement? In modern operating systems, processes often require more memory than is physically available (RAM). The OS uses virtual memory to handle this, dividing memory into fixed-size blocks called pages. Only a few pages can be kept in RAM at a time — the rest are stored on secondary storage (e.g., disk).
